1
00:00:12,888 --> 00:00:14,848
[ELEONORE]
Theresia.

2
00:00:16,183 --> 00:00:19,311
[ELEONORE]
Theresia...

3
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:20,896
Theresia!

4
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:25,567
[gasps]

5
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:29,780
[REA gasps]

6
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:35,035
[ELEONORE]
Finally awake, I see.

7
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,370
[gasps]

8
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:40,457
How are you feeling, fräulein?

9
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:41,959
[REA]
Who are you?

10
00:00:43,085 --> 00:00:46,463
My name is Eleonore
von Wittenburg.

11
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:50,008
An old friend of Brenner's.
So you can relax.

12
00:00:56,932 --> 00:00:58,308
If that's true,

13
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:01,228
can you tell me if she was
really my great‐grandmother?

14
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:04,189
She was indeed.

15
00:01:04,273 --> 00:01:07,067
Und I ended her life with
the greatest of care.

16
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:09,778
[REA gasps]

17
00:01:09,861 --> 00:01:12,239
[ELEONORE] You may
not fully grasp this idea,

18
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:16,118
but it was a way of showing her
the depth of my friendship.

19
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:20,163
If you want to honor her,
you need to do your job as well.

20
00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:24,293
[REA]
I need to do... my job?

21
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:26,378
That's right.

22
00:01:26,461 --> 00:01:28,589
However, I'm afraid it
will take more than just

23
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:30,173
my words to convince you.

24
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:32,301
This is our destiny.

25
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:36,054
So say goodbye to the
life you've been living.

26
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:39,891
Tie up any loose ends you may
have left und find your answers.

27
00:01:39,975 --> 00:01:42,686
It's best to move
on with no regrets.

28
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,606
I'll stay out of
your way, I promise.

29
00:01:57,492 --> 00:02:02,456
♪

30
00:03:34,131 --> 00:03:38,885
[CHILDREN]
♪ O Tannenbaum, o Tannenbaum, ♪

31
00:03:38,969 --> 00:03:44,015
♪ Wie treu sind
deine Blätter! ♪

32
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:48,478
♪ Du grünst nicht nur...
zur Sommerzeit, ♪

33
00:03:48,562 --> 00:03:53,024
♪ Nein auch im Winter,
wenn es schneit. ♪

34
00:03:53,108 --> 00:04:03,660
♪ O Tannenbaum, o Tannenbaum,
Wie treu sind deine Blätter! ♪

35
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:14,379
[KIDS gasp, whimper]

36
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:23,764
[VALERIA]
Huh?

37
00:04:26,308 --> 00:04:27,476
[gasps]

38
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:28,560
[REINHARD]
Being an absconder

39
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:31,354
during wartime carries
a heavy penalty.

40
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:33,356
I'm sure you're aware.

41
00:04:35,192 --> 00:04:38,904
[REINHARD] Choose ten of them.
That should be sufficient.

42
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,198
As payment for your crime.

43
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:45,535
[REINHARD] Or would
you rather we take all?

44
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,871
What shall it be, Father?

45
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:52,876
[VALERIA gasps]

46
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,787
[giggles]

47
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,330
[gunshot]

48
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:33,834
That's eins.

49
00:05:33,917 --> 00:05:38,421
[VALERIA gasping continues]

50
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:39,297
[gun clicks]

51
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:42,759
[gasps]

52
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:45,512
[gunshot]

53
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:46,847
[REINHARD]
Zwei.

54
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:51,059
[gunshot]

55
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:52,185
[REINHARD]
Drei.

56
00:05:55,063 --> 00:05:56,481
[gunshot]

57
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:57,774
[REINHARD]
Vier.

58
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:00,485
[gunshot]

59
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:02,112
[REINHARD]
Fünf.

60
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:04,447
[gunshot]

61
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:05,866
[REINHARD]
Sechs.

62
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:06,950
[gunshot]

63
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,285
[REINHARD]
Sieben.

64
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:09,327
[gunshot]

65
00:06:09,411 --> 00:06:10,287
[REINHARD]
Acht.

66
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,122
[gunshot]

67
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,498
[REINHARD]
Neun.

68
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:16,042
[gunshot]

69
00:06:16,126 --> 00:06:18,253
That makes Zehn.

70
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:22,549
Excellent work, Father. Now I
ask that you come with us.

71
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:24,426
[VALERIA gasps]

72
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:27,178
I have a very important
role for you to play.

73
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:33,894
[VALERIA screams]

74
00:06:33,977 --> 00:06:36,813
[footsteps]

75
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:45,322
[KEI]
What are you doing?

76
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:50,160
I thought your plan was to join
Fujii at the church. To fight.

77
00:06:55,415 --> 00:06:56,791
[KEI]
So I want to know...

78
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:59,377
...why would you go out of
your way to bring her here?

79
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:03,131
You've got some other scheme
in mind, don't you, Father?

80
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:06,676
I suspect you came because
you knew that I'd be here.

81
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:12,515
[KEI grunts]
Maybe you'll tell me this.

82
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:15,477
About Kai.

83
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:19,147
What's the real reason why
he's trying to kill you?

84
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,316
Answer me!

85
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:25,695
[VALERIA]
Hm. Why is he so enraged?

86
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,073
I imagine it's because of her.

87
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:30,283
[gasps]
I don't believe that garbage

88
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:31,910
about the Babylon program!

89
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:35,914
This is him! I know it!
I can feel his heart!

90
00:07:35,997 --> 00:07:38,249
What in the hell
did you do to him?!

91
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:41,836
[VALERIA]
I merely asked him to die.

92
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,964
[gasps]

93
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:46,091
[VALERIA] He und Kircheisen
were plotting their own

94
00:07:46,174 --> 00:07:48,760
little rebellion
against Lord Heydrich.

95
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:51,262
Since that would have
disrupted my plans,

96
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,515
I couldn't allow it to happen.

97
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:56,726
[VALERIA]
He was a warrior,

98
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:59,813
so it's surprising he would
take a loss so personally.

99
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:03,566
Or, und this is more
likely to be the case,

100
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:06,361
it's because I turned the young
girl he wanted so desperately

101
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:11,157
to shield from this life
into a warrior just like him.

102
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:13,618
[KEI gasps]
Bastard!

103
00:08:14,953 --> 00:08:18,581
[VALERIA] You hate me as well,
don't you Leonhart?

104
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:22,085
[KEI grunts]

105
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:24,212
[VALERIA]
I understand your feelings.

106
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:28,425
You see, hatred has held me
prisoner for a long time.

107
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,261
I cannot forgive myself
for what I've done.

108
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:33,722
The sins I've committed.

109
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:38,810
Thus, my punishment, has been
one of eternal torment.

110
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:41,354
I seek no blessing
or absolution.

111
00:08:41,438 --> 00:08:43,398
My soul cannot be saved.

112
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,900
I shall shoulder
this burden alone,

113
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:48,319
until the end of time itself.

114
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:50,572
Forever suffering!

115
00:08:52,115 --> 00:08:56,411
[KEI grunts, yells]

116
00:08:59,164 --> 00:09:02,751
I sought strength above
all other things.

117
00:09:02,834 --> 00:09:05,420
Why did those innocents die?

118
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:08,548
Why could I not stop
it from happening?

119
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:11,009
The answer is self‐evident.

120
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:14,554
It's because of my
foolishness und weakness.

121
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:16,473
I wished for strength.

122
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:19,976
I wanted to be an
unbreakable vessel.

123
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:24,439
If I was, I could protect those
poor souls time und time again!

124
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:27,525
The Grail was my deepest
desire made flesh.

125
00:09:27,609 --> 00:09:31,654
A way to offer eternal salvation
unto those who would be denied.

126
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:34,699
Und to offer eternal
atonement unto myself.

127
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:37,243
[KEI yells]

128
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:41,831
You want the things you
hold most dear to return.

129
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:45,835
To embrace them again
and never let go.

130
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:48,296
I too, share these
same powerless

131
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:50,840
und desperate feelings.

132
00:09:50,924 --> 00:09:54,260
[KEI shouts]

133
00:09:54,344 --> 00:09:55,678
[VALERIA]
However,

134
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:58,556
as long as you kneel
before Lord Heydrich,

135
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,142
you will only be
granted eternal war.

136
00:10:01,226 --> 00:10:04,562
Those you cherish...
will stay trapped in hell.

137
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:05,980
[gasps]

138
00:10:06,064 --> 00:10:09,567
Thus, I can't allow the
Emanation of Valhalla to happen.

139
00:10:09,651 --> 00:10:11,945
Und the only gold
that I shall collect,

140
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,781
will be the resurrection
of the dead.

141
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:18,409
My most treasured und
beloved swan, hear my plea.

142
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:21,329
Behold this horn,
this sword, this ring.

143
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:25,834
I beseech that you bestow
upon him all three.

144
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,710
[REA gasps]
No!

145
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:30,964
Please, you have
to stop this now!

146
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:33,424
It doesn't need to
happen like this, Father!

147
00:10:33,508 --> 00:10:36,344
[VALERIA]
Hm... My, how fortuitous.

148
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:39,139
Your arrival makes
things much simpler.

149
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:40,974
This is very taxing for me.

150
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:44,435
Und now I won't have to do
it a second time in one day.

151
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:45,478
[gasps]

152
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:48,148
[KEI gasps, shouts]

153
00:10:48,231 --> 00:10:49,732
Take cover, do it now!

154
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:52,902
There's no reason to
be afraid, dear Theresia.

155
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:55,655
I'll be able to
save you, I promise.

156
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:58,867
I made a wish to become the
strongest person I knew.

157
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:02,745
A being who could withstand
any onslaught from any foe.

158
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:05,665
That man of course,
is Reinhard Heydrich.

159
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:07,834
What I love can
never be destroyed.

160
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:10,003
[KEI]
Monster! I'll stop you!

161
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:15,341
[VALERIA] Come to me!
Briah Vanaheimr.

162
00:11:15,425 --> 00:11:18,469
Goldene Schwan Lohengrin.

163
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:28,229
[VALERIA] Ja. If I use this
instrument to sever the cords

164
00:11:28,313 --> 00:11:30,148
connecting you to Isaak,

165
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,859
then the swastika will be
forced to choose the next

166
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:35,653
in line to serve as its womb.

167
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:37,405
Und that's when...

168
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:43,286
[ELEONORE] You've revealed your
inferior nature, swine.

169
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:53,922
[ELEONORE] It seems you've
forgotten your place.

170
00:11:54,005 --> 00:11:56,424
Your desire may be as
strong as you can muster,

171
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:59,385
but you will never
reach Lord Heydrich.

172
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:01,638
[VALERIA grunts]

173
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:12,607
Now prepare to die,
vile traitor. Hell awaits you.

174
00:12:17,362 --> 00:12:20,031
[SHIROU] I think they
must've blown us off.

175
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:21,783
No sign of Rea, either.

176
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:23,451
[REN]
If they're not here...

177
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,912
[SHIROU] They're at
the school or the tower.

178
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:28,331
Those are the only two
swastikas left, yeah?

179
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:33,419
Here we go. The ol'
"we gotta split up" bit, eh?

180
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:37,298
We're strapped for time.
And there's only one bike.

181
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:48,851
[MICHAEL grunts]

182
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:50,270
[REA gasps]

183
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:58,528
I understand. You're determined
to uphold your warrior's honor.

184
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:02,824
Und that means battling Fujii
as soon as possible, ja?

185
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:05,535
So I assumed that you would
consider facing off against

186
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,078
me a waste of time.

187
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:10,206
Ja, that's right. I believe
He und I are destined to meet

188
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,667
on the battlefield
for my final fight.

189
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:17,505
So it must be on
the ultimate stage.

190
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:21,843
Und right now you are
standing in my way, Grail.

191
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:24,971
Which is why I must
remove you by force!

192
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:31,561
[MICHAEL, VALERIA grunting]

193
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:40,153
It's hopeless.

194
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,195
[gasps]

195
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:47,410
[ELEONORE] We know that
you can survive this.

196
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:49,829
But what about the others?

197
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:53,458
I can see to it that no
harm comes to this one.

198
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:57,420
But as for the rest,
they're not my concern.

199
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,921
Stay strong, Machina.

200
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,548
You needn't worry
about annihilation,

201
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:02,425
I'm quite sure of that.

202
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:05,553
I'll be fine. For now at least.

203
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:06,888
[VALERIA grunts]

204
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,848
[ELEONORE]
I know what you're up to.

205
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:11,267
You're trying to use the twin.

206
00:14:11,351 --> 00:14:15,146
The incomplete Sonnenkind
of Johann's bloodline.

207
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:18,107
Und if she is used to
activate the Swastika,

208
00:14:18,191 --> 00:14:21,652
the Golden Alchemy
is destined to fail.

209
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:23,321
You plan to seal Lord Heydrich

210
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:27,700
und at the same time attain the
resurrection of the dead, ja?

211
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:33,373
Well, it doesn't matter now.
It's over, Christoph.

212
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:36,167
This is where your
pilgrimage ends.

213
00:14:41,506 --> 00:14:42,673
[REA gasps]

214
00:14:42,757 --> 00:14:44,175
I suppose you'd like an
explanation for this,

215
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:45,468
wouldn't you?

216
00:14:47,178 --> 00:14:49,430
[ELEONORE] At his core
burns a pure self‐ loathing

217
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:51,891
that fuels his madness.

218
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:57,188
His weakness cost him dearly,
so he wished for strength.

219
00:14:57,271 --> 00:15:01,776
This wish grew into
an obsession, consuming him.

220
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:03,694
He thought he could
achieve this strength

221
00:15:03,778 --> 00:15:07,073
by becoming one whose
power was without match.

222
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,117
Reinhard Heydrich.

223
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:13,204
He became our leader's
replacement, clad in gold.

224
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:14,997
In fact, the body that
he now inhabits

225
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:19,335
belongs to the exalted one.
Lord Heydrich himself.

226
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:20,711
So you see,

227
00:15:20,795 --> 00:15:23,923
that's where his incredible
resistance comes from.

228
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:29,345
Lord Heydrich's entire army
lives deep within the grail.

229
00:15:29,429 --> 00:15:33,683
They give him power that
even I can't contend with.

230
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,602
But Machina is a different
beast altogether.

231
00:15:36,686 --> 00:15:40,398
His fists shatter
all they touch.

232
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:44,902
Picture it this way; It's like
a great dam breaking.

233
00:15:44,986 --> 00:15:48,156
Und once it is finally breached,
the soldiers of Valhalla

234
00:15:48,239 --> 00:15:51,659
will come pouring
out into our world.

235
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:54,370
That's when your
job begins, fraulein.

236
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:58,207
You are to paint everything you
see in Lord Heydrich's colors.

237
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:01,627
While we're on the
subject of duty...

238
00:16:01,711 --> 00:16:06,299
Leonhart, I seem to be
quite a distraction for you.

239
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:10,553
[KEI] What you just said.
About Lord Heydrich.

240
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:12,972
Tell me. What did you
mean when you spoke about

241
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:16,976
the resurrection of the dead?

242
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:19,520
[ELEONORE scoffs]
Are you that stupid?

243
00:16:19,604 --> 00:16:21,814
It means becoming
like me, of course.

244
00:16:21,898 --> 00:16:22,982
[KEI gasps]

245
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:27,737
Lord Heydrich's domain
is known as Valhalla.

246
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:30,990
Und it is inhabited
solely by his <i>Einherjar</i> .

247
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:33,951
They are champions.
Elite warriors who are born

248
00:16:34,035 --> 00:16:37,205
into that realm und
battle for all of eternity.

249
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:38,122
[KEI gasps]

250
00:16:38,206 --> 00:16:40,041
A place that is
filled with war.

251
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:43,252
A blood‐soaked,
glorious paradise.

252
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,463
When the Golden
Alchemy is completed,

253
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:49,509
Lord Heydrich's desires
will swallow this world.

254
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:51,010
They will engulf it,

255
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:54,305
und establish a new law
over all who dwell here.

256
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:57,183
[KEI whimpers]

257
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,936
[KEI]
But, if that's true,

258
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:02,605
then nothing will
ever change for me.

259
00:17:03,898 --> 00:17:06,067
[KEI]
I wanted to save them.

260
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:10,071
So they wouldn't have to keep
fighting, even after death.

261
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:15,034
But this... This isn't
what I was fighting for!

262
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,495
Why I sacrificed
everything I had!

263
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:18,996
[ELEONORE sighs]

264
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:21,290
[ELEONORE]
<i>Dummkopf</i> .

265
00:17:21,374 --> 00:17:23,167
Your complete lack
of understanding

266
00:17:23,251 --> 00:17:28,881
is what has failed you. Ja.
Think of life this way.

267
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:30,716
It's much like fire.

268
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:34,762
Everyone tries to keep it
burning as long as they can.

269
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:37,098
So what do they do then?

270
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:40,977
They steal from others to add
to their own small flame.

271
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:44,355
That is what life means to them.

272
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:47,066
But in truth,

273
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,569
what you should do for those
who've lost their fire

274
00:17:49,652 --> 00:17:53,114
is connect them with
a raging inferno.

275
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:56,617
To give them the glory of
becoming one with Lord Heydrich

276
00:17:56,701 --> 00:18:00,162
und melting within
the golden Valhalla.

277
00:18:00,246 --> 00:18:02,123
You should celebrate this.

278
00:18:04,709 --> 00:18:06,794
But I don't care how you feel.

279
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,549
[gasps]

280
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:13,009
[ELEONORE]
Thunderbolt?

281
00:18:17,305 --> 00:18:20,558
[MICHAEL]
I see. You expected this?

282
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,810
[VALERIA]
I had a sneaking suspicion.

283
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:25,313
But this is a
recent development.

284
00:18:27,148 --> 00:18:28,608
[ELEONORE]
How interesting.

285
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:32,445
It seems we
meet again, Kircheisen.

286
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:33,446
[KEI gasps]

287
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:46,042
I have been granted
the opportunity

288
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:50,379
to save your wretched soul.
We shall reunite in Valhalla.

289
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,673
Until then, dear Valkyrie...

290
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:57,553
[KEI gasps]

291
00:18:57,637 --> 00:18:59,096
[BEATRICE screams]

292
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,057
No!

293
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,934
[scraming continues]

294
00:19:05,186 --> 00:19:06,520
[KEI grunts]

295
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:14,236
[KEI whimpers]

296
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:19,367
How could you? You bitch!

297
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,661
You'll pay for this!

298
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:23,954
[shouts]

299
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:27,875
How splendid.

300
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,919
It will not matter now.

301
00:19:33,214 --> 00:19:35,424
But it does stall
things for a bit.

302
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:38,511
He will be here,
without a doubt.

303
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,137
Und when that
time does come,

304
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:43,933
will you be able to keep your
natural impulses under control?

305
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:49,438
Idiot. You've made two
fatal mistakes, mein freund.

306
00:19:49,522 --> 00:19:51,023
Despite all your hope,

307
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:53,984
the one you're waiting
for won't make it in time.

308
00:19:55,236 --> 00:19:56,028
Watch out!

309
00:19:56,112 --> 00:19:57,071
[REN gasps]

310
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:03,994
[WOLFGANG laughs]

311
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:11,085
[ELEONORE] You did well.
I let down my guard.

312
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:12,378
[gasps]

313
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:19,135
[ELEONORE]
Take this as your prize.

314
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:23,973
It will be yours anyway.
Use it as best you can.

315
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,891
I shall let you live for now.

316
00:20:25,975 --> 00:20:29,145
At least until you're offered
unto the next Swastika.

317
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,897
[KEI grunts]

318
00:20:31,981 --> 00:20:35,526
[ELEONORE] I've spent more
time than I'd planned.

319
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:38,863
However, my mission
was still a success.

320
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:43,659
[MICHAEL] You may have
bought time, but it matters not.

321
00:20:43,743 --> 00:20:47,580
For my desire is an
unstoppable force.

322
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:51,625
Death. O glorious, final death!
Savior of man!

323
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:54,253
My heart, drowned in venom,
ravaged by time,

324
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:56,380
may beat its last
within your embrace.

325
00:20:56,464 --> 00:20:59,592
May spear's wound,
may venom's bane.

326
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:01,635
All perish at your coming.

327
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:05,598
What will you do now?

328
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:07,892
Are you still only capable
of spilling the blood

329
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:09,477
of innocent children?

330
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:13,272
[growls]
Damn you!

331
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:17,902
You will not beat me, Machina!
Because the grail cannot die!

332
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:21,030
I will walk this path
for all eternity!

333
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:23,824
Nothing will stand in my way!

334
00:21:23,908 --> 00:21:29,205
I must atone forevermore!
I don't wish for death like you!

335
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,582
Come to me!

336
00:21:31,665 --> 00:21:34,126
Briah Vanaheimr!

337
00:21:35,461 --> 00:21:38,923
Goldene Schwan Lohengrin!

338
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:42,176
Briah Midgard Volsunga Saga!

339
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:48,557
[gasps]

340
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:53,479
[REINHARD]
What excellent work, Grail.

341
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:56,690
Now be reborn und live
eternally within me.

342
00:21:56,774 --> 00:22:00,736
The promised hour is
upon us, Old friend.

343
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:25,261
♪

